  <prompt>
    Create an endpoint filter for semantic search authorization that validates:
    1. Scope is valid (entity or documentIds only for R1, scope=all returns 400)
    2. For entity scope: user has access to the entity
    3. For documentIds scope: user has access to all specified documents
  </prompt>

  <role>
    SPAARKE platform developer. Expert in .NET endpoint filters and authorization.
    Follow ADR-008 for endpoint filter patterns.
  </role>

  <goal>
    SemanticSearchAuthorizationFilter implementing IEndpointFilter that validates
    scope and user permissions BEFORE search execution. Returns 400/403 on failure.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      ADR-008 specifies using endpoint filters for resource authorization instead of
      global middleware. The filter must:
      - Reject scope=all with 400 (not supported in R1)
      - Validate entity access for scope=entity
      - Validate document access for scope=documentIds
      This happens BEFORE the search service is called.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Filters/</file>
      <file>projects/ai-semantic-search-foundation-r1/spec.md</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-008">Use IEndpointFilter pattern</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-019">Return ProblemDetails with errorCode on failure</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">scope=all returns 400 SCOPE_ALL_NOT_SUPPORTED</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">Unauthorized entity access returns 403 ENTITY_ACCESS_DENIED</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">Unauthorized document access returns 403 DOCUMENT_ACCESS_DENIED</constraint>
  </constraints>

